ized Labor in America: A Biographical Study''. Westport, Connecticut: Greenwood Press.\n* Rogers, James Silas and Matthew J O'Brien, eds. ''After the Flood: Irish America, 1945\u20131960'' (2009), Specialized essays by scholars\n* Sim, David. (2013) ''A Union Forever: The Irish Question and US Foreign Relations in the Victorian Age'' ([[Cornell University Press]], 2013)\n\n===Protestant Irish===\n* Blaustein, Richard. '' The Thistle and the Brier: Historical Links and Cultural Parallels Between Scotland and Appalachia'' (2003).\n* Blethen, Tyler; Wood, Curtis W. Jr.; Blethen, H. Tyler (Eds.) (1997). ''Ulster and North America: Transatlantic Perspectives on the Scotch-Irish''. Tuscaloosa, Alabama: [[University of Alabama Press]]. {{ISBN|0-8173-0823-7}}\n* Cunningham, Roger (1991). ''Apples on the Flood: Minority Discourse and Appalachia''. Knoxville, Tennessee: University of Tennessee Press. {{ISBN|0-87049-629-8}}\n* Esbenshade, Richard. \"Scotch-Irish Americans.\" in ''Gale Encyclopedia of Multicultural America'', edited by Thomas Riggs, (3rd ed., vol. 4, Gale, 2014), pp. 87-100. [https://link.gale.com/apps/doc/CX3273300156/GPS?u=wikipedia&sid=GPS&xid=27347afb Online free]\n* [[David Hackett Fischer|Fischer, David Hackett]] (1991). ''[[Albion's Seed: Four British Folkways in America]]''. New York: Oxford University Press USA. {{ISBN|0-19-506905-6}}\n* Ford, Henry Jones (1915). ''The Scotch-Irish in America''. [https://archive.org/details/irishinamer00fordrich Full text online].\n* Griffin, Patrick (2001). ''The People with No Name: Ireland's Ulster Scots, America's Scots Irish, and the Creation of a British Atlantic World, 1689\u20131764''. Princeton, New Jersey: Princeton University Press. {{ISBN|0-691-07462-3}}\n* Kenny, Kevin (2000). ''The American Irish: A History''. New York: Longman, 2000. {{ISBN|978-0582278172}}\n* Leyburn, James G. (1989). ''The Scotch-Irish: A Social History''. Chapel Hill: University of North Carolina Press. {{ISBN|0-8078-4259-1}}\n* Lorle, Porter (1999). ''A People Set Apart: The Scotch-Irish in Eastern Ohio''. Zanesville, Ohio: Equine Graphics Publishing. {{ISBN|1-887932-75-5}}\n* McWhiney, Grady (1988). '' Cracker Culture: Celtic Ways in the Old South''. Tuscaloosa: University of Alabama Press. {{ISBN|0-8173-0328-6}}\n* Ray, Celeste. ''Highland Heritage: Scottish Americans in the American South'' (2001).\n* Webb, James H. (2004). ''Born Fighting: How the Scots-Irish Shaped America''. New York: Broadway. {{ISBN|0-7679-1688-3}}.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.connectireland.com/ ConnectIreland : dedicated to create new jobs in Ireland by harnessing the power of the global Diaspora]\n* [http://www.irishamerica.com/ ''Irish America'' magazine]\n* [http://www.irishvoice.com/ ''Irish Voice''], newspaper for Irish Americans\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061106224031/http://www.irishemigrant.com/Boston/ The Boston Irish Emigrant]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060115063519/http://www.irishemigrant.com/NY/ The New York Irish Emigrant]\n* [http://www.icphila.org/ Irish Immigration Center of Philadelphia]\n* [http://www.aoh.com/ Ancient Order of Hibernians]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/keyword/irish-american IMDb.com Irish-American]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060604140515/http://www.irlfunds.org/ The Ireland Funds]\n* [http://www.eiresociety.org/ The Eire Society of Boston]\n* [http://philly.thedrinknation.com/articles/read/10198-Top-Irish-Bars-in-Philadelphia#/ Philadelphia Irish Bars]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150223175225/http://www.ppfpd.org/ Philadelphia Police and Fire Pipes and Drums]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150128132539/http://www.philadelphiaemeraldsociety.com/ Philadelphia Emerald Society]\n* [http://www.emeraldpipers.com/ Philadelphia Emerald Society Pipe Band]\n* [http://www.secondstreetirishsociety.org/ Philadelphia Second Street Irish Society]\n* [http://www.wearethatband.com/ Philadelphia Second Street Irish Society Pipes and Drums]\n* [https://web.archive.org