ick, Joby; and Sill, Melanie (February 19, 1995). [https://web.archive.org/web/20081006120012/http://www.pulitzer.org/archives/5892 \"Boss Hog: The power of pork\"], ''The News & Observer'' (Raleigh) (this and the following articles on the pig industry in North Carolina won the [[Pulitzer Prize for Public Service]] in 1996):\n:*Stith, Pat and Warrick, Joby (February 19, 1995). [https://web.archive.org/web/20081006120017/http://www.pulitzer.org/archives/5893 \"New studies show that lagoons are leaking\"], ''The News & Observer''.\n:*Stith, Pat and Warrick, Joby (February 21, 1995). [https://web.archive.org/web/20081006120022/http://www.pulitzer.org/archives/5896 \"Corporate takeover\"], ''The News & Observer''.\n:*Stith, Pat and Warrick, Joby (February 22, 1995). [https://web.archive.org/web/20081006120027/http://www.pulitzer.org/archives/5897 \"Murphy's Law\"], ''The News & Observer''.\n:*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081006120032/http://www.pulitzer.org/archives/5898 \"Hog-Tied on ethics\"], ''The News & Observer'', editorial, February 23, 1995.\n:*Stith, Pat and Warrick, Joby (February 24, 1995). [https://web.archive.org/web/20081006120037/http://www.pulitzer.org/archives/5899 \"Money Talks\"], ''The News & Observer''.\n:*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081006120042/http://www.pulitzer.org/archives/5900 \"Putting the hush on hogs\"], ''The News & Observer'', editorial, February 24, 1995.\n:*Stith, Pat and Warrick, Joby (February 26, 1995). [https://web.archive.org/web/20081006120048/http://www.pulitzer.org/archives/5901 \"Pork Barrels\"], ''The News & Observer''.\n:*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081006120053/http://www.pulitzer.org/archives/5902 \"When hogs come first\"], ''The News & Observer'', editorial, February 28, 1995.\n*Wing, Steve et al. (October 2008). \"Air Pollution and Odor in Communities near Industrial Swine Operations\", ''Environmental Health Perspectives'', 116(10), pp.&nbsp;1362\u20131368. {{jstor|25071189}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{pigs}}\n{{ham}}\n{{